# Classifier Extension Self-Test — late_ack_after_trigger_completed

generated_at=2026-05-27
goal=frames/codex-goals/classifier-extend-late-ack-after-trigger-completed-goal-20260527.md

## Scope

Adds `INFRA_ROOT_LATE_ACK_AFTER_TRIGGER_COMPLETED` to the classifier, detection
function, harness-side default `defaultLateAckResolver` (filesystem + git
work-at-HEAD check), and integration into `decideRetryAction` so that late-ack
runs whose work is already at HEAD resolve to `final_pass_via_late_ack`
instead of unnecessarily retrying.

Verifier was NOT modified.

## Unit tests

command:
  node --test scripts/runner-classify-infra-failure.test.mjs

result=PASS, 12/12 tests pass, 0 failures.

New tests added:
- `classifier reclassifies late_ack_after_trigger_completed from fail_verifier to infra_retry`
- `classifier does NOT reclassify normal passing run as late_ack (ack < completed)`
- `harness retry policy resolves late_ack to final_pass when work is at HEAD`
- `harness retry policy retries late_ack when work is NOT at HEAD`
- `T7 medium ledger run 014 reclassifies to infrastructure_retry with late_ack root cause`

## T7 medium ledger reclassification

WITH late-ack resolution (default in harness CLI):
```
pass_count: 13
agent_failure_count: 0
infra_retry_count: 4
late_ack_resolved_count: 1
total_run_attempts: 17
pass_rate_percent: 100.0
infrastructure_failure_rate_percent: 23.5
```

WITHOUT late-ack resolution (`--no-resolve-late-ack`):
```
pass_count: 12
agent_failure_count: 0
infra_retry_count: 5
total_run_attempts: 17
pass_rate_percent: 100.0
infrastructure_failure_rate_percent: 29.4
```

Both views agree on agent_failure_count=0 (Maya was previously mis-attributed
as the cause of run 014; the classifier extension correctly attributes it to
the Pentagon defect). The difference is whether the work-at-HEAD evidence
demotes run 014 from `infrastructure_retry` to `pass`.

